Design a next-generation, award-winning, high-end interactive website for a digital agency called **4O4 Solutions**.

This website must NOT feel like a template, dashboard, or standard startup landing page. It must feel like a cinematic digital experience built for Awwwards-level interaction design.

The design must be bold, experimental, and deeply interactive with strong identity expression. The brand personality is futuristic, intelligent, creative, and slightly “glitchy-premium”.

Primary palette: **white + vibrant orange + subtle dark contrast accents**. Orange is not decoration — it is a dynamic energy system used for motion, glow, interaction, and focus states.

---

# CORE EXPERIENCE RULES

## 1. The entire website is a story-driven scroll experience

Scrolling is not navigation — it is progression through a digital narrative.

Each section transitions like a cinematic scene change with:

* parallax depth layers
* soft zoom transitions
* motion-based reveal storytelling
* controlled scroll pacing (not fast layout jumps)

---

## 2. HERO SECTION — “4O4 DIMENSIONAL CORE”

The hero is not static.

It contains a **Three.js living 3D core object** that:

* reacts to mouse movement
* morphs shape dynamically
* emits subtle particle trails
* distorts based on scroll velocity

On scroll:

* the core splits into fragments
* each fragment represents a site section (Projects, Services, Testimonials, Contact)
* fragments move toward their section positions as the user scrolls

The hero must feel like:

> “This is the brain of the entire website”

---

## 3. HEADER — “MORPHING GLASS NEURAL NAV”

The navigation is a living system:

* glassmorphism with dynamic blur based on scroll
* logo transforms with subtle glitch pulse on interaction
* nav links have magnetic hover behavior
* header changes state based on section context (Projects / Services / etc.)
* cursor interaction slightly distorts the header layer

It must feel embedded into the system, not floating on top.

---

## 4. PROJECTS — “INTERACTIVE CASE STUDY TUNNEL”

This is the most important section.

Projects are NOT cards or grid items.

Instead:

* each project is a full viewport cinematic scene
* scroll transitions between projects like Apple product storytelling pages
* each project includes:

  * large cinematic visual (image/video)
  * bold headline
  * short result metric (impact-focused)
  * subtle background motion layers
* hover reveals deeper detail layer with smooth expansion

The experience should feel like:

> “Walking inside a portfolio museum”

---

## 5. SERVICES — “STRUCTURED INTELLIGENCE GRID”

Services are displayed as interactive intelligent modules:

* hover-based 3D tilt
* radial glow interaction from cursor
* animated feature chips
* numbered progression system (01–06)
* each service feels like a capability engine, not a list

---

## 6. TESTIMONIALS — “FLOATING TRUST LAYERS”

Testimonials are not static cards.

They exist in layered depth space:

* one primary focused testimonial at a time
* background testimonials float with blur and reduced opacity
* smooth automatic transitions between testimonials
* subtle motion breathing effect
* emotional tone emphasized through typography hierarchy

---

## 7. SPACING SYSTEM — “BREATHING DESIGN”

Spacing must follow cinematic rhythm:

* large vertical breathing spaces (20vh section separation)
* asymmetric layouts to avoid template feel
* intentional empty space as part of storytelling
* no rigid grid repetition

Every section must feel like a scene, not a block.

---

## 8. MOTION LANGUAGE

Motion must be:

* smooth, slow, cinematic
* scroll-reactive (not just animation-on-load)
* depth-based (z-axis movement)
* layered (foreground/background separation)

Avoid generic UI transitions.

---

## 9. MOBILE EXPERIENCE

Mobile is NOT simplified desktop.

Instead:

* restructured storytelling flow
* stacked cinematic scenes
* reduced Three.js complexity but preserved identity
* swipe-based project navigation feel

---

# FINAL RESULT

The final product must feel:

* like a high-end digital agency experience
* emotionally engaging and interactive
* deeply custom and non-template
* award-winning level UI/UX
* immersive, cinematic, and futuristic

The goal is not to show information.

The goal is to create an experience users remember.
